PROJECT REFLECTION :

While building my digital portfolio, I created and updated profiles on GitHub, LinkedIn, and Kaggle. What surprised me most was how each platform serves a completely different purpose—GitHub focuses on showcasing actual work, LinkedIn builds professional identity and connections, and Kaggle supports practical learning in data science through real datasets.

Initially, I underestimated the importance of maintaining a clean and complete profile, but I realized that recruiters often judge candidates based on their online presence before even interacting with them. Setting up my GitHub profile README and organizing it properly was particularly interesting, as it acts like a live resume.

Over the next four years, I plan to consistently upload projects on GitHub, actively network and share achievements on LinkedIn, and improve my machine learning skills through Kaggle competitions. This task helped me understand that building a strong digital presence is a continuous process and a key factor in securing internships and career opportunities.
